    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "An uncle is not a `block`. An uncle is a `header`. Therefore, a block can contain N uncles. Whereas, if an uncle were a block, then a block containing uncles (blocks) would be a recursive definition. \r\nSo it has a `transactionsRoot` (which is a header field), but does not have the actual `transactions` (which is a part of the block body)",
